{
  "texts": [
    "Below, we report a brief explanation to justify their choice.",
    "The Slope carries the signal of the gravitational pull acting on potentially unstable materials hanging along the topographic profile (Taylor, 1948).",
    "Elevation, Eastness and Northness are common proxies for a series of processes such as moisture, vegetation, and temperature (Clinton, 2003), and their effect on slope stability (Neaupane and Piantanakulchai, 2006; Whiteley et al., 2019; Loche et al., 2022).",
    "As for the Planar and Profile Curvatures, these are known to control the convergence and divergence of overland flows (Ohlmacher, 2007).",
    "This hydrological information is also supported by the Topographic Wetness Index and Distance to River (Yesilnacar and Topal, 2005)."
  ]
}